1
00:01:39,070 --> 00:01:40,950
♪ Booo-il, boil, boil! ♪

2
00:01:40,950 --> 00:01:43,000
♪ Booo-il, boil, boil! ♪

3
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:45,910
♪ Boil, boil! Boil, bo-iiil! ♪

4
00:01:47,420 --> 00:01:51,400
Chobro, help! It's hot!

5
00:01:51,950 --> 00:01:55,460
Stop whining, you brat!

6
00:01:55,460 --> 00:01:57,760
I don't eat humans, but...

7
00:01:58,590 --> 00:02:01,600
minks could be edible,
so I gotta try.

8
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:04,720
Don't eat me! I'm not delicious!

9
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:07,280
Let Carrot go, Brûlée!

10
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:11,400
She's not a real rabbit!
Of course, she's not delicious!

11
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:13,500
What? Is that true?

12
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,680
He's right!

13
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:16,440
Then, maybe I shouldn't try.

14
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:16,440
I'm too tough and stinky and disgusting!

15
00:02:18,630 --> 00:02:23,740
I'm not gonna let her go.
Keep your mouth shut, you odd reindeer.

16
00:02:23,740 --> 00:02:27,300
You'll join Mama's collection
of strange beasts!

17
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:30,000
C-Collection of strange beasts?

18
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:34,580
That's right. So just sit there quietly.

19
00:02:42,470 --> 00:02:46,330
Okay! We managed to get to this point.

20
00:02:47,310 --> 00:02:49,250
I made sure to get tied up in Heavy Point,

21
00:02:49,250 --> 00:02:53,530
so I could escape from these
chains instantly by transforming.

22
00:02:53,530 --> 00:02:57,940
I'm giving Chopper trouble!
Pedro will be mad at me!

23
00:02:57,940 --> 00:03:03,940
It's been at least six hours since I used Monster
Point yesterday, so that's at my disposal, too!

24
00:03:03,940 --> 00:03:06,240
♪ When the delicious soup is ready, ♪

25
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:07,790
♪ dump her in! ♪

26
00:03:07,790 --> 00:03:09,750
♪ Booo-il, boil, boil! ♪

27
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:11,120
♪ Booo-il, boil, boil! ♪

28
00:03:11,150 --> 00:03:13,000
♪ Booo-il, boil, boil! ♪

29
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,480
♪ Booo-il, boil, boil! ♪

30
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:16,670
♪ She's gonna be delicious! Let's try! ♪

31
00:03:17,180 --> 00:03:18,670
♪ Booo-il, boil, boil! ♪

32
00:03:18,670 --> 00:03:21,470
♪ Booo-il, boil, boil! Puff, puff! ♪

33
00:03:22,590 --> 00:03:24,390
Chobro!

34
00:03:24,390 --> 00:03:26,140
Now's the chance!

35
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:44,080
Here it is.

36
00:03:46,710 --> 00:03:50,800
Within books, you can find an infinite array of worlds.

37
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:56,250
Look. This is a super-rare, man-eating lion
with a human face.

38
00:03:57,040 --> 00:03:58,760
A manticore.

39
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:01,580
It's a strange beast that
escaped from Impel Down

40
00:04:01,580 --> 00:04:04,960
during Blackbeard's assault two years ago.

41
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:07,660
Loincloth, loincloth!

42
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:07,660
It moved!

43
00:04:07,660 --> 00:04:10,680
And this one is my pride and joy!

44
00:04:13,610 --> 00:04:15,600
Isn't it beautiful?

45
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:19,440
Well... close enough. But it's living in the book.

46
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:24,160
The animals within the books will never age.

47
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:30,620
It makes sense, right?
The contents of a book never change.

48
00:04:30,620 --> 00:04:32,320
Help!

49
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:40,800
The books in this library contain
rare creatures from all over the world.

50
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:41,880
Cool!

51
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:45,630
That's what my son, Mont d'Or, is capable of.

52
00:04:45,630 --> 00:04:49,470
Recently, we got a centaur from Punk Hazard,

53
00:04:49,470 --> 00:04:52,680
and a griffin from the South Blue.

54
00:04:53,650 --> 00:04:55,770
I even got one of these!

55
00:04:55,770 --> 00:04:57,820
A long-limbed human!

56
00:04:57,820 --> 00:04:59,360
Help!

57
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:01,730
Let me out!

58
00:05:02,150 --> 00:05:03,650
Even a human?

59
00:05:05,370 --> 00:05:07,200
Big Mom.

60
00:05:07,950 --> 00:05:13,890
Since I stepped into this country,
I've seen a wide variety of races.

61
00:05:13,890 --> 00:05:19,440
Of course! Because that's the kind of country
that Totto Land is supposed to be!

62
00:05:19,440 --> 00:05:24,800
But there is one race that I haven't seen,
and I haven't been able to stop thinking about it.

63
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:27,980
If they were here, we would know.

64
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,140
The giants!

65
00:05:32,310 --> 00:05:38,230
For a nation of all races,
it's odd that I haven't seen a single giant.

66
00:05:38,230 --> 00:05:41,070
I've only seen large humans.

67
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:51,580
Oh, really?

68
00:05:52,140 --> 00:05:55,180
I guess you just haven't seen one yet.

69
00:05:55,180 --> 00:05:57,220
Mama!

70
00:05:59,670 --> 00:06:01,070
What do you want?

71
00:06:01,070 --> 00:06:07,760
Ma... Mama... Ma, we... we... we have
brought those... those two here!

72
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:10,820
Okay.

73
00:06:11,220 --> 00:06:14,340
Will you excuse me? It's a very busy day.

74
00:06:14,340 --> 00:06:18,080
I hope you have a good afternoon, despite the bad weather!

75
00:06:20,550 --> 00:06:22,010
What's wrong with you?

76
00:06:22,010 --> 00:06:24,730
W-Well, I got nervous.

77
00:06:24,730 --> 00:06:27,890
They're the real Germa 66.

78
00:06:27,890 --> 00:06:32,450
Ichiji and Reiju were just as cool
as I thought they'd be.

79
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:39,580
Shut up! You're foolish to have been
influenced by a comic strip!

80
00:06:39,580 --> 00:06:43,040
That they look "cool" couldn't matter less.

81
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:49,000
Let's see, what page was it?

82
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,090
Page 55.

83
00:06:52,420 --> 00:06:53,930
Fifty-five.

84
00:06:53,930 --> 00:06:55,590
There they are.

85
00:06:55,590 --> 00:06:59,020
These two? I like the look on their faces.

86
00:06:59,020 --> 00:07:01,190
Lick!

87
00:07:03,060 --> 00:07:05,420
How long are you gonna keep us like this?!

88
00:07:05,420 --> 00:07:06,900
Let me take a shower!

89
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:09,610
My body is covered in sticky syrup!

90
00:07:09,610 --> 00:07:14,530
You look so sweet, Candy-chan. Lick!

91
00:07:16,700 --> 00:07:18,740
Here comes Mama.

92
00:07:18,740 --> 00:07:19,870
What?

93
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:25,710
Huh?

94
00:07:25,710 --> 00:07:27,420
A transponder snail?!

95
00:07:34,790 --> 00:07:38,700
It's been a while, Straw Hat Luffy!

96
00:07:38,700 --> 00:07:41,560
You finally made it this far.

97
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:43,440
Is this Big Mom?

98
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:47,560
Let me out! I gotta go back!

99
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:50,860
I'm gonna get out of here,
even if I have to destroy everything!

100
00:07:53,350 --> 00:07:57,800
Whoa-whoa, you've still
got that kind of spirit.

101
00:07:58,290 --> 00:08:01,460
Since you didn't bring your entire crew,

102
00:08:01,460 --> 00:08:06,920
I thought you'd forgotten what you said to me
on Fishman Island.

103
00:08:07,300 --> 00:08:10,420
I'll kick your ass in the New World...

104
00:08:10,420 --> 00:08:14,090
and make Fishman Island my territory!

105
00:08:15,250 --> 00:08:18,600
Yeah, I'll kick your ass someday!

106
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:22,900
But right now we're just here
to take back Sanji!

107
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:26,190
I've had enough of your bluffs!

108
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:40,160
Shut up!
If you wanna fight, show yourself, Big Mom!

109
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:47,540
I'll fight you... right here!

110
00:08:55,630 --> 00:08:58,600
Hey! Come on, Big Mom!

111
00:09:00,810 --> 00:09:02,430
Show yourself!

112
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:07,020
I'll fight you!

113
00:09:09,070 --> 00:09:11,440
Don't push your luck.

114
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:16,530
You're a rookie who just
entered the New World.

115
00:09:16,530 --> 00:09:20,450
It's presumptuous of you
to request an audience with me.

116
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:28,670
They don't need my help in killing you.

117
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:36,470
Listen carefully, Straw Hat.

118
00:09:37,930 --> 00:09:44,390
If you give up on Sanji completely,
I'll let you leave with your head.

119
00:09:44,390 --> 00:09:45,850
Screw that!

120
00:09:48,520 --> 00:09:51,980
Sanji and Pudding's wedding

121
00:09:51,980 --> 00:09:53,640
is very...

122
00:09:53,640 --> 00:09:56,190
special to me.

123
00:09:58,700 --> 00:10:04,950
So sit there quietly
until everything is over.

124
00:10:09,830 --> 00:10:15,590
Straw Hat, if you spoil what
I've been looking forward to,

125
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:22,050
I'll really make you pay for it!

126
00:10:25,850 --> 00:10:27,310
Oh, yeah!

127
00:10:28,020 --> 00:10:30,190
Do you remember?

128
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:35,320
When you ate all of the candy
that was made for me,

129
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:41,990
you gave me all the treasure
that you got from King Neptune.

130
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:44,980
We've got tons of treasure here.

131
00:10:46,050 --> 00:10:50,050
I'll give all of it to you
as compensation for the candy!

132
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:58,880
Guess what we found in there!

133
00:11:02,860 --> 00:11:05,350
Don't say that you want it back!

134
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:09,460
It's a legendary treasure box
that was passed down for

135
00:11:09,460 --> 00:11:12,270
generations on Fishman Island:

136
00:11:12,270 --> 00:11:14,770
the Tamate Box.

137
00:11:18,780 --> 00:11:23,080
I wonder why Neptune let go of it.

138
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:28,580
It's certainly a national treasure.
I wonder what's in it.

139
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:36,760
I love treasure boxes!

140
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:41,300
So forget about the candy.

141
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:46,850
I'm going to open the Tamate Box
in front of everyone at the tea party tomorrow.

142
00:11:48,490 --> 00:11:51,140
It's gonna be fun!

143
00:11:51,140 --> 00:11:55,270
It's not gonna be fun! Sanji won't get married!

144
00:11:56,610 --> 00:11:59,070
Damn!

145
00:11:59,070 --> 00:12:01,400
Oh, yeah! I wanna see Pudding!

146
00:12:00,860 --> 00:12:02,920
Luffy! Don't mention her!

147
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:04,700
I need to talk to her! She's my friend!

148
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:07,830
Huh? Friend?

149
00:12:10,170 --> 00:12:15,040
Don't be absurd.
Why would the bride be your friend?

150
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:19,330
Luffy!

151
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:21,970
Stop joking around!

152
00:12:21,970 --> 00:12:23,880
By the way, girl,

153
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:28,720
I heard you killed Lola.

154
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:32,090
What are you talking about?!
She's my friend!

155
00:12:32,090 --> 00:12:35,960
She gave me the vivre card
as a token of friendship!

156
00:12:36,150 --> 00:12:39,340
I'll put my signature on Mama's vivre card,

157
00:12:39,340 --> 00:12:43,500
so if you run into trouble,
you can use this to find her.

158
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:46,900
When you see her, tell her I'm doing fine.

159
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:49,240
Thanks, Lola.

160
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:52,000
Lola was doing fine.

161
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:55,330
That's the message she sent.
There, I delivered it.

162
00:12:55,830 --> 00:12:58,750
She told me that her mother was a pirate,

163
00:12:58,750 --> 00:13:02,010
but I didn't expect that
it'd be Emperor Big Mom.

164
00:13:02,590 --> 00:13:07,010
Lola thought that if I showed you
the vivre card, you'd help me...

165
00:13:07,010 --> 00:13:10,220
You've gotta be joking!

166
00:13:23,150 --> 00:13:25,890
I don't care if she's "doing fine."

167
00:13:25,890 --> 00:13:27,220
I want her dead!

168
00:13:27,220 --> 00:13:28,160
What?!

169
00:13:28,620 --> 00:13:31,030
If you know where she is, tell me.

170
00:13:31,030 --> 00:13:34,790
I'll send an assassin right away to kill her!

171
00:13:34,790 --> 00:13:39,000
I'm surprised by the fact
she still thinks that we're family!

172
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:43,100
Children don't know how indebted they are
to their parents, and this proves it!

173
00:13:43,100 --> 00:13:49,260
She's a dumb daughter who ran away,
rejecting the biggest-ever political marriage!

174
00:13:50,260 --> 00:13:52,470
I'll never forgive her!

175
00:13:55,280 --> 00:14:00,110
One of you can have me as a wife!
Especially you! Won't you marry me?!

176
00:14:00,880 --> 00:14:04,860
Absalom is gonna marry me!

177
00:14:04,860 --> 00:14:08,840
You're perfect for each other!
I thought I could give you all my support!

178
00:14:08,840 --> 00:14:11,720
What?! Really?!

179
00:14:12,090 --> 00:14:15,450
I'm here to save you, my friend!

180
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,500
Lola!

181
00:14:19,940 --> 00:14:23,250
Lola! I'm so glad I got to see you again!

182
00:14:23,250 --> 00:14:29,270
It's just for you,
because you and I are like sisters.

183
00:14:30,860 --> 00:14:32,560
Lola...

184
00:14:35,100 --> 00:14:36,220
If only...

185
00:14:36,930 --> 00:14:41,100
she'd done what I said
and gotten married,

186
00:14:41,100 --> 00:14:44,020
I could've gained tremendous power!

187
00:14:44,020 --> 00:14:50,410
I'd already have beaten Kaido,
Red Hair, and even Whitebeard,

188
00:14:50,410 --> 00:14:52,320
and I'd already be...

189
00:14:52,950 --> 00:14:57,290
king of the pirates!

190
00:15:07,060 --> 00:15:12,220
Lola's friend, Cat Burglar Nami.

191
00:15:13,550 --> 00:15:17,930
I'll make you cough up where she is.

192
00:15:20,420 --> 00:15:23,810
What a stupid story, Big Mom.

193
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:30,780
Lola's the one who didn't get married.

194
00:15:33,490 --> 00:15:37,770
You're the one who
hasn't become king of the pirates.

195
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:41,370
That's all.

196
00:15:43,830 --> 00:15:45,710
Luffy...

197
00:15:45,710 --> 00:15:48,090
I'm here to pick another fight with you!

198
00:15:48,090 --> 00:15:52,010
Don't be cocky just because
you're an emperor!

199
00:15:52,010 --> 00:15:54,600
I'm going to take Sanji back!

200
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:58,850
And in the end, we're the ones who'll win!

201
00:16:18,030 --> 00:16:20,030
What's going on-soir ?

202
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:27,520
Baron Tamago, it's the intruder!

203
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:30,010
The tiger mink is here!

204
00:16:30,010 --> 00:16:32,260
No, he's a jaguar mink!

205
00:16:32,260 --> 00:16:37,260
Pedro... He's already in the castle, as I thought.

206
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:40,680
Hey, wait, Big Mom!

207
00:16:42,390 --> 00:16:43,980
You're so funny!

208
00:16:45,560 --> 00:16:47,570
You've got to be kidding!

209
00:16:47,570 --> 00:16:51,830
How could you pick a fight
with Mama in this castle?!

210
00:16:51,830 --> 00:16:54,740
Shut up! Bring it on, you bastards!

211
00:16:57,570 --> 00:16:58,830
Lola...

212
00:17:04,620 --> 00:17:08,750
Hey, Big Brothers and Sisters!
Coming through! Coming through!

213
00:17:09,180 --> 00:17:11,920
Anglaise, what's up?

214
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:20,300
We have an intrudee in the treasure room!
Coming through!

215
00:17:21,230 --> 00:17:23,770
Do you mean an intruder, Anglaise?

216
00:17:23,770 --> 00:17:24,980
Yeah, that's it!

217
00:17:24,980 --> 00:17:29,560
And I'm not gonna brush my teeth today!
Coming through!

218
00:17:37,410 --> 00:17:39,030
Please...

219
00:17:39,420 --> 00:17:42,080
Everyone, get out of here safely.

220
00:17:43,900 --> 00:17:45,710
Don't let him get away!

221
00:17:57,590 --> 00:17:59,260
Get a move on!

222
00:17:59,260 --> 00:18:01,940
Don't let him do whatever he wants!

223
00:18:01,940 --> 00:18:04,890
The intruder's in the other area!

224
00:18:06,150 --> 00:18:11,610
And now, in the Pirate Emperor
Big Mom's castle...

225
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:16,730
it's time to start...

226
00:18:16,730 --> 00:18:19,410
a special live performance!

227
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:27,500
Aren't you angry, Mama?

228
00:18:29,330 --> 00:18:32,750
Just because that squirt
picked a fight with me?

229
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:37,840
No way, Zeus! Think about it!

230
00:18:42,260 --> 00:18:46,560
♪ Tomorrow, I'll gain Germa's power, ♪

231
00:18:46,560 --> 00:18:51,100
♪ and even the Tamate Box... ♪

232
00:18:53,360 --> 00:18:56,230
♪ I'll eat the most delicious ♪

233
00:18:56,230 --> 00:18:59,600
♪ wedding cake ever, too! ♪

234
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:01,070
♪ Right? ♪

235
00:19:01,070 --> 00:19:04,910
♪ That's right! ♪

236
00:19:04,910 --> 00:19:09,210
♪ If I think of tomorrow, ♪

237
00:19:09,210 --> 00:19:13,290
♪ I can tolerate anything! ♪

238
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:18,170
♪ How can I be angry?! ♪

239
00:19:18,170 --> 00:19:22,470
♪ Tomorrow is going to be a great day! ♪

240
00:19:22,470 --> 00:19:27,390
♪ A happy day! ♪

241
00:19:28,430 --> 00:19:32,310
Oh? I received a signal. Mama!

242
00:19:32,310 --> 00:19:35,660
They say that an intruder is causing trouble
near the treasure repository!

243
00:19:35,660 --> 00:19:37,490
An intruder?

244
00:19:37,490 --> 00:19:39,730
♪ Wedding cake! ♪

245
00:19:39,730 --> 00:19:42,070
♪ Queen of the cakes! ♪

246
00:19:42,070 --> 00:19:46,240
♪ Wedding cake! ♪

247
00:19:50,210 --> 00:19:54,130
Don't tell me they're going after my Tamate Box!

248
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:57,300
Who is it?!

249
00:19:59,210 --> 00:20:01,630
Oh, dammit, dammit!

250
00:20:01,630 --> 00:20:05,540
Luffy and the others will be spared.
Big Mom promised me.

251
00:20:05,540 --> 00:20:08,770
As long as I get married,
the Baratie will be okay, too.

252
00:20:10,350 --> 00:20:14,380
Of course, it's hard to say goodbye to my friends,
but at least nobody will die!

253
00:20:14,380 --> 00:20:16,300
That's all that really matters!

254
00:20:17,250 --> 00:20:19,150
So, why am I so upset?

255
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:22,150
If I keep looking so tense,

256
00:20:22,150 --> 00:20:25,370
my only source of hope,
Pudding-chan, will be sad!

257
00:20:27,910 --> 00:20:32,000
I won't let your marriage with me be hell!

258
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:40,000
I'll be the lowest form of scum
if I make her worry.

259
00:20:42,260 --> 00:20:47,240
Don't let a lovely girl like her be sad!
Be my usual self!

260
00:20:47,240 --> 00:20:50,430
Yes! I'm a romantic cook!

261
00:20:50,430 --> 00:20:52,500
Pudding-chan !

262
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:55,790
Pudding-chwan !

263
00:20:55,790 --> 00:20:59,900
I'll make you happy!

264
00:21:02,620 --> 00:21:04,220
Big Sis Lola's?

265
00:21:04,220 --> 00:21:08,160
Yes. The girl had her vivre card,

266
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:12,750
and the homies in the Seducing Woods
were intimidated by it.

267
00:21:13,360 --> 00:21:19,210
By the way, Madam Pudding,
the dress you chose yesterday was rejected by Mama.

268
00:21:19,210 --> 00:21:23,010
Tomorrow, please wear the dress Mama chose.

269
00:21:23,430 --> 00:21:27,030
Mama has planned out everything
after the wedding, too.

270
00:21:27,030 --> 00:21:28,050
Also...

271
00:21:31,850 --> 00:21:34,890
Madam Pudding, it's still raining in the yard.

272
00:21:35,340 --> 00:21:36,810
Madam Pudding?

273
00:21:40,990 --> 00:21:46,030
Pudding, as long as you do
what I say, you'll be all right.

274
00:21:46,780 --> 00:21:52,040
You look just like a doll, Pudding.

275
00:21:52,140 --> 00:21:55,150
Good girl, Pudding.

276
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:14,430
She's not gonna kill me.
After all, we're family.

277
00:22:14,430 --> 00:22:18,100
I wanna choose my own husband!

278
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:38,000
I can't believe they let this happen
the day before the tea party!

279
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:48,130
There he is!

280
00:22:55,620 --> 00:22:57,140
So quick!

281
00:23:09,950 --> 00:23:12,030
This is it, intruder!

282
00:23:25,170 --> 00:23:26,920
Shoot!

283
00:23:34,470 --> 00:23:36,220
Shoot him down!

284
00:23:43,310 --> 00:23:45,570
Run!

285
00:24:01,130 --> 00:24:03,290
Where is he now?!

286
00:24:03,290 --> 00:24:05,840
He went downstairs
to the third floor of the midbaum,

287
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:07,670
near the courtyard!

288
00:24:07,670 --> 00:24:12,800
It won't be easy to take him down!
Corner him in the garden-soir !

289
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:14,060
Roger!

290
00:24:18,900 --> 00:24:23,770
I can't handle any more soldiers!

291
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:27,480
There you are, intruder.

292
00:24:30,210 --> 00:24:34,450
Well, there are a lot less than before.

293
00:24:34,450 --> 00:24:37,240
Only Pedro-san could've done that!

294
00:24:38,580 --> 00:24:41,020
What kind of creature are you?

295
00:24:41,020 --> 00:24:45,370
You're very strange, even for this country.

296
00:24:46,130 --> 00:24:47,960
I agree.

297
00:24:48,850 --> 00:24:50,840
Mama would be happy.

298
00:24:52,260 --> 00:24:55,090
Get him!

299
00:24:57,180 --> 00:24:59,180
Hey, Baron Tamago!

300
00:24:59,180 --> 00:25:00,860
Commander Smoothie!

301
00:25:00,860 --> 00:25:03,940
You were right. There's another one.

302
00:25:03,940 --> 00:25:06,440
That one is bait, like you said.

303
00:25:07,450 --> 00:25:10,690
Damn you, Pedro!
You created a big mess!

304
00:25:11,860 --> 00:25:16,750
We let him get into the treasure repository,
and then he locked the door.

305
00:25:16,750 --> 00:25:18,660
Sorry. It's my fault.

306
00:25:18,660 --> 00:25:22,000
But there is only one entrance
to the treasure repository.

307
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:28,670
Even if he can steal the treasure, it's impossible for him to run from you, Commander Smoothie.

308
00:25:28,670 --> 00:25:32,550
As long as you guard the door closely,
there won't be a problem-dezvous.

309
00:25:32,550 --> 00:25:35,660
You're right. You can count on me.

310
00:25:35,660 --> 00:25:41,810
If he defeats the guards inside and comes out,
I'll kill him. Is that okay?

311
00:25:41,810 --> 00:25:47,870
No, the man inside is probably a skeleton-bon.
Mama would love to have that strange beast.

312
00:25:47,870 --> 00:25:50,760
Defeat him, but don't kill him!

313
00:25:50,760 --> 00:25:52,650
Got it.

314
00:26:04,140 --> 00:26:07,290
Pedro-san told me...

315
00:26:07,290 --> 00:26:09,280
that through Big Mom's ability,

316
00:26:09,280 --> 00:26:13,090
you are all infused with human souls.

317
00:26:13,090 --> 00:26:16,550
That means you Chess Peacekeepers are...

318
00:26:19,340 --> 00:26:22,640
driven by soul!

319
00:26:24,240 --> 00:26:25,810
Oh, no!

320
00:26:26,310 --> 00:26:28,950
How powerful!

321
00:26:28,950 --> 00:26:30,770
Wait a second!

322
00:26:30,770 --> 00:26:33,190
It's not tuned yet!

323
00:26:33,190 --> 00:26:36,920
Tear him apart!

324
00:26:43,330 --> 00:26:46,540
This is it, you damn skeleton!

325
00:26:48,460 --> 00:26:50,210
Oh, please!

326
00:26:50,210 --> 00:26:52,540
W-W-W-W-Wait, wait!

327
00:26:56,510 --> 00:26:59,090
Please wait!

328
00:27:21,800 --> 00:27:23,490
What happened?!

329
00:27:23,490 --> 00:27:29,210
You don't know my other name,
do you, baby?

330
00:27:43,110 --> 00:27:45,890
They call me Soul King!

331
00:27:53,160 --> 00:27:55,230
The Chess Peacekeepers!

332
00:27:55,230 --> 00:27:58,400
The soldiers infused with souls...

333
00:27:59,900 --> 00:28:05,030
cannot stay on their feet...

334
00:28:05,030 --> 00:28:08,490
in the presence of my Soul Scream!

335
00:28:21,760 --> 00:28:24,390
Enough with that!

336
00:28:32,810 --> 00:28:35,520
Oh, this is unexpected.

337
00:28:35,930 --> 00:28:38,690
What do you need, Pudding?

338
00:28:40,080 --> 00:28:41,150
Pudding?

339
00:28:45,490 --> 00:28:50,370
Hey! Pudding! Get us outta here! We got caught!

340
00:28:48,280 --> 00:28:50,370
No, Luffy!

341
00:28:50,370 --> 00:28:52,330
The other guys are listening too!

342
00:28:52,330 --> 00:28:55,960
What brought you to a place like this?

343
00:28:58,060 --> 00:29:04,090
Brother Opera, do you mind if I talk to Luffy-kun
and his companion for a moment?

344
00:29:04,090 --> 00:29:09,510
Luffy-kun ? Sure, go ahead.

345
00:29:12,350 --> 00:29:14,730
Let me put a bookmark here.

346
00:29:25,140 --> 00:29:26,240
Pudding...

347
00:29:27,890 --> 00:29:29,740
You two...

348
00:29:31,310 --> 00:29:32,950
Hey, Pudding!

349
00:29:32,950 --> 00:29:35,300
We went to the coast!

350
00:29:35,300 --> 00:29:38,670
Stop it! Pudding will be in trouble!

351
00:29:42,190 --> 00:29:43,840
You got beaten up.

352
00:29:45,280 --> 00:29:46,550
Luffy-kun.

353
00:29:46,550 --> 00:29:48,740
Nami-chan.

354
00:29:50,080 --> 00:29:54,430
I'm sure my brothers and sisters
did horrible things to you.

355
00:29:55,810 --> 00:29:57,770
I'm sorry!

356
00:29:58,380 --> 00:30:00,190
– No...
– Don't...

357
00:30:01,760 --> 00:30:05,120
I couldn't go to the coast
where we promised to meet, either...

358
00:30:05,120 --> 00:30:06,750
I'm really sorry!

359
00:30:06,750 --> 00:30:10,740
That's okay. Raise your head, please.

360
00:30:12,810 --> 00:30:16,210
Why are they whispering?

361
00:30:17,540 --> 00:30:20,330
I actually...

362
00:30:21,420 --> 00:30:26,230
was proposed to by Sanji-san.

363
00:30:26,230 --> 00:30:28,030
– What?!
– What?!

364
00:31:02,410 --> 00:31:04,460
It made me happy.

365
00:31:05,570 --> 00:31:06,800
But...

366
00:31:07,630 --> 00:31:11,760
I know Sanji-san is just being nice to me.

367
00:31:13,630 --> 00:31:16,350
I'm causing everyone trouble.

368
00:31:16,350 --> 00:31:17,520
That's not true...

369
00:31:21,590 --> 00:31:24,320
So, don't worry.

370
00:31:25,070 --> 00:31:28,610
I'm not going to marry him.

371
00:31:36,130 --> 00:31:37,500
Listen.

372
00:32:03,850 --> 00:32:05,400
Hey, wait, Pudding!

373
00:32:16,630 --> 00:32:18,270
Goodbye.

